{{Infobox painting|image=Monet_dejeunersurlherbe.jpg|title=Le Déjeuner sur l’herbe|medium=oil on canvas|museum=[[Musée d'Orsay]]|artist=Claude Monet}}
'''''Le Déjeuner sur l’herbe''''' (English - ''Dinner on the Grass'') is an 1865-1866 oil on canvas painting by [[Claude Monet]], produced in response to the 1863 [[Le Déjeuner sur l’herbe|work of the same title]] by [[Édouard Manet]]. It remained unfinished, but two large fragments are now in the [[Musée d’Orsay]] in Paris.

Monet included the artist [[Gustave Courbet]] in the painting.

